🧩 1. Core Stack Around FastAPI

🔹 What
FastAPI alone is just the API layer. A real backend needs:
(FastAPI is a python framework like express for node.js or nest for node.js but not exactly like them )

Database
ORM
Auth
Config
Background jobs
Caching
Deployment

(
Uvicorn
Pydentic -> data validation libray like typscript and much more
mac -> python3, windows/linux -> python

venv (virtual environment)
requirements.txt

Decorator

alembic
poetry
Starlette -> for web handling
)


🔹 Why

Because FastAPI ≠ full ecosystem like NestJS
👉 You assemble your own stack (more flexible, but more decisions)


| Feature         | NestJS           | FastAPI Equivalent        |
| --------------- | ---------------- | ------------------------- |
| Framework       | NestJS           | FastAPI                   |
| ORM             | TypeORM / Prisma | SQLAlchemy / Tortoise ORM |
| Validation      | class-validator  | Pydantic                  |
| Auth            | Passport.js      | JWT / OAuth libs          |
| Background Jobs | Bull             | Celery                    |
| Cache           | Redis            | Redis                     |
| Config          | @nestjs/config   | python-dotenv             |

ORM (Object-Relational Mapping) is a tool that lets you talk to a database using code (objects) instead of writing raw SQL.

🏗️ 2. Project Structure (FastAPI version of NestJS)
🔹 What

FastAPI doesn’t enforce structure—you create it.

🔹 How (recommended structure)
app/
 ├── main.py          # entry point
 ├── api/             # routes (controllers)
 ├── models/          # DB models
 ├── schemas/         # request/response (DTOs)
 ├── services/        # business logic
 ├── db/              # database connection
 ├── core/            # config, security

👉 This is basically NestJS modules broken manually


🧠 3. Database Layer
🔹 What

You need an ORM to talk to DB.




FastAPI is very fast for Python because it uses ASGI, what is ASGI? Uvicorn?alembic? poetry?Starlette? for?

What

These are the core building blocks around FastAPI.

Think like this:

FastAPI is like NestJS/Express
and these tools are the ecosystem around it.

1. ASGI
What

ASGI = Asynchronous Server Gateway Interface

It is the modern standard for running Python web apps.

It is like the “bridge” between:

your FastAPI app
and the web server handling requests
Simple Node comparison
Old Python way
Flask/Django → WSGI → Server
Modern Python way
FastAPI → ASGI → Server
Node way
Express/NestJS → Node Runtime → Server
Why ASGI matters

Because ASGI supports:

async/await
WebSockets
long connections
high concurrency
non-blocking I/O

This is why FastAPI is fast.

2. Uvicorn
What

Uvicorn is the actual server that runs FastAPI.

Like:

uvicorn main:app --reload

means:

“Start my FastAPI app”

Node comparison
Python
FastAPI + Uvicorn
Node
Express + Node runtime

So:

Uvicorn = runtime/server for FastAPI

3. Starlette
What

Starlette is the lightweight framework underneath FastAPI.

FastAPI is built on top of Starlette.

It handles:

routing
middleware
requests
responses
background tasks
WebSockets
Simple meaning
FastAPI = Starlette + Pydantic + extra features


4. Alembic
What

Alembic is used for:

Database migrations

Like:

create table
add column
update schema
Node comparison
Python
SQLAlchemy + Alembic
Node
TypeORM/Prisma + migrations

Same concept.

5. Poetry
What

Poetry is for:

package management
dependency management
virtual environments
locking versions
Node comparison
Python
Poetry
Node
npm / yarn / pnpm

Very similar.

Super Easy Summary:

| Tool      | Meaning            | Node Equivalent           |
| --------- | ------------------ | ------------------------- |
| ASGI      | async app standard | Node runtime architecture |
| Uvicorn   | runs FastAPI app   | node server runtime       |
| Starlette | base framework     | Express core              |
| Alembic   | DB migrations      | Prisma/TypeORM migrations |
| Poetry    | package manager    | npm/yarn                  |
